<concept id="concept_E8D43EB4494E41D2AB42D4A89396D1AB"
                    xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>User Management</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p
                conref="../../overview/whatiscmm/c-userroles.xml#concept_E8D43EB4494E41D2AB42D4A89396D1AB/is_fully_integrated_with_Key_concept_conbody_section_2_p"/>
            <p>The <ph conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    /> integration with Keystone requires any <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    /> user, including the Monitoring Service operator, to be registered as an OpenStack user. All authentication and authorization in <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    /> is done through Keystone. If a user requests monitoring data, for example, <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                /> verifies that the user is a valid user in OpenStack and allowed to access the requested metrics.</p>
            <p
                conref="../../overview/whatiscmm/c-userroles.xml#concept_E8D43EB4494E41D2AB42D4A89396D1AB/users_are_created_and_admini_concept_conbody_section_2_p"/>
            <ul
                conref="../../overview/whatiscmm/c-userroles.xml#concept_E8D43EB4494E41D2AB42D4A89396D1AB/Each_user_assumes_a_role_in_O_concept_conbody_section_2_ul">
                <li/>
            </ul>
            <p>For details on user management, refer to the <xref
                format="html" href="http://docs.openstack.org/newton/"
                scope="external"><u><i>OpenStack documentation</i></u></xref>.</p>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
